{"word":"προσφύω","slug":"προσφύω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>προσφύω</b></el> <el>(<a href='S:future tense'>fut.</a> <el>-φύσω</el>) (aor1 <el>-έφῡσα</el>) </el><p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>to make to grow to</i>: <a href='S:metaphorically'>metaph.</a> <i>to make sure, confirm</i>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a> or <a href='S:Medium, Middle'>Mid.</a>, <i>to grow to</i> or <i>upon</i>, <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:dative'>dat.</a>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b>:—<a href='S:metaphorically'>metaph.</a> <i>to cling to</i>, <el>τῷ προσφὺς ἐχόμην</el> <b><a href='S:Odyssey'>Od.</a></b>; and <a href='S:absolute, absolutely'>absol.</a>, <el>προσφῦσα</el> <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b>; of a fish, <el>τὠγκίστρῳ ποτεφύετο</el> <b><a href='S:Theocritus'>Theocr.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}